{"title": "Beneath Suspicion", "content": "\"Brick, down in the gutter, had dropped below even that horizon. No wonder Chrysoprase's shakedown hadn't corralled him. Brick was something you stepped over.\"\n\nA character who is linked with all the victims of a crime spree is not even regarded as a suspect by the detectives until halfway through the final act. The reasons why this character is never considered vary, but boils down to the trope name itself: they're beneath suspicion. The idea that someone so kind, or so quiet, or so stupid could possibly be the culprit seems so asinine that no one considers it, much less find it worth pursuing, until every other option has been exhausted.\n\nOften seen in conjunction with Never One Murder. More often than not ruined in live action by a familiar face.\n\nPretty much endemic in murder mysteries, especially British ones like Taggart, Midsomer Murders, et al. Done properly, the writer will be able to fool even the audience, who regard everybody with suspicion \u0097 even the detectives.\n\nSource of The Butler Did It. See also The Dog Was the Mastermind, Beneath Notice.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeneathSuspicion", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TerryPratchett", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Taggart", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MidsomerMurders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BatmanEternal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Daredevil", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Superman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/LexLuthor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/TheShadow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/WonderWoman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Hoodwinked", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ScaryMovie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HotFuzz", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SawI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MurderByDeath", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Fresh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GosfordPark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheUsualSuspects", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AmericanAnimals"